dataStructures

Class DynamicList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • dataStructures.DynamicList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Reference-type object type for the list

    public class DynamicList<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    DynamicList is a generic dynamic list for objects. It follows ArrayList's behaviour and is implemented as an array.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DynamicList

        public DynamicList()
        Creates a new DynamicList and initiates the array. Initial backing array size 10. Initial DynamicList size 0.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public void add(E e)
        Adds an element to the end of the list. List size grows by one.
        Parameters:
        e - Element to be appended to this list.

      • add

        public void add(int index,
                E object)
        Inserts the specified element at the specified position in this list. Shifts the element currently at that position (if any) and any subsequent elements to the right (adds one to their indices). List size grows by one.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the list where the object is to be inserted
        object - The object to be inserted

      • get

        public E get(int index)
        Returns but does not remove the element at the given index. Throws an IndexOutOfBoundsException if the index is not valid.
        Parameters:
        index - Index of the element to be returned.
        Returns:
        E The object found at the parameter index.

      • remove

        public E remove(int index)
        Removes the element at the given index. Shifts any subsequent elements to the left (subtracts one from their indices).
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the element to be removed
        Returns:
        E The object found and removed from the index

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clears the list. Backing array size set to 10 and DynamicList size to 0.

      • size

        public int size()
        Returns the number of elements on the list.
        Returns:
        int Returns the number of elements on the list

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if the list size is zero, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        boolean Returns true if the size of the list is zero, false if not.
